(37, 'Termessos & Düden Waterfalls Tour', 'Termessos--Duden-Waterfalls-Tour', '630c4-duden-waterfall-1920x1080.jpg', '7310c-termessos-national-park.jpg', '2030', 26, '<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">09:00 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Meeting and move from Antalya Kaleici head office.</span></small></big></span></div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">09:50&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Arrival to the ancient city of Termessos G&uuml;ll&uuml;k Mountain, 40 km North-West of Antalya.</span></small></big></span></div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">10:00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; After a 30 min.Climming, we will reached the peak of the ancient city Termessos. Following the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">tourof the ancient city which lasts for two hours. İn total we have min. tree hours for Termesseos</span></small></big></span></div>\n<pre>\n</pre>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">13:15&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Return to the city Antalya.</span></small></big></span></div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">14:00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Arrival at the D&uuml;den Waterfall. Time one hour to visit the National Park and take break for a lunch.</span></small></big></span></div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">15:30&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Move back to Antalya.</span></small></big></span></div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:roboto,sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">16:00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Return to the Hotels.</span></small></big></span></div>\n', '<p color:=\"\" font-size:=\"\" list-style:=\"\" open=\"\" outline:=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \" text-align:=\"\">\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The first stop of the day will be the Ancient City of Termessos, built by the Solymianson the shipping route to the Aegean. Built totally on a mountainous area, we will take our time to explore some of the remains including the walls, the Hadrian&#39;s triumphal arch, cisterns, theatre, the gymnasium, agora, the Odeon and the Heroon. Among the tombs which are scattered far and wide can be seen the extraordinary sites of Alcates, Agatemeros and the Lion decorated sarcophagi.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\n	<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\n	<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; background-color: initial;\">Termessos lies in Gulluk Dag National Park which includes an area for breeding wild goats and deer, and may be the last refuge of the Anatolian lynx. If we are lucky we may also spot the many butterflies that inhabitant here.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\n	<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\n	<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; background-color: initial;\">After a delicious lunch we will continue to see Duden Waterfalls, a group of waterfalls in the province of Antalya, Turkey. The waterfall, formed by the Duden River (one of the major rivers in southern Anatolia) is located 12 km north-east of Antalya, which ends where the crystal waters of the Lower Duden Falls drop off a rocky cliff directly into the Mediterranean Sea.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\n	<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\n	<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; background-color: initial;\">Following a large day of site-seeing you will be dropped back to your hotel at 17:00.</span></span></span></p>\n', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Sports or walking shoes are preferred.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Transfer service from the Hotel.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Travel with comfortable air conditioned minibus and the presence of a professional guide.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Travel incurence are inclueded. </span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Lunch is inclusive, &nbsp;drinks are excluded.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Entrance Fees are inclusive.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span font-size:=\"\" helvetica=\"\" segoe=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 43, 73); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \">Head office in Antalya.</span></span></span></p>\n', '', '7 Hours', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">English speaking tour guide.</span></p>\n', 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\">24 hours before the tour.</span></span></p>\n', 1, '', 'surekli', 0, '', 1, '', '<div>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><big><small>&nbsp;</small></big>Termessos &amp; D&uuml;den Waterfalls Tour ,&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: roboto, sans-serif;\"><big><small><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Arrival to the ancient city of Termessos G&uuml;ll&uuml;k Mountain, 40 km North-West of Antalya.&nbsp;</span></small></big></span><span style=\"font-family: roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">After a 30 min.Climming, we will reached the peak of the ancient city Termessos. Following the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">tourof the ancient city which lasts for two hours. İn total we have min. tree hours for Termesseos&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: roboto, sans-serif;\">Return to the city Antalya.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: roboto, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Arrival at the D&uuml;den Waterfall. Time one hour to visit the National Park and take break for a lunch.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: roboto, sans-serif;\">Move back to Antalya.</span></div>\n', 1, 1, '12+', '6-12', '0-5', 0, 31, 'Termessos & Düden Şelalesi Turu', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Tur g&uuml;zergahı ve saati aşağıda g&ouml;sterilmiştir,</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">09:00 Antalya Kalei&ccedil;i merkez b&uuml;rosunda toplanma ve hareket etme.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">09:50 Antalya&#39;nın 40 km kuzeybatısındaki antik Termessos G&uuml;ll&uuml;k Dağı kentine varış.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">10:00 30 dk sonra Antik kent Termessos&#39;un zirvesine &ccedil;ıkacağız. İki saat s&uuml;ren antik kent gezisinin ardından toplamda Termessos i&ccedil;in 3 saatimiz var.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">13:15 Antalya şehrine d&ouml;n&uuml;ş.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">14:00 D&uuml;den Şelalesi&#39;ne varış. Milli Parkı ziyaret etmek ve &ouml;ğle yemeği molası vermek i&ccedil;in bir saat s&uuml;re.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">15:30 Antalya&#39;ya geri d&ouml;n&uuml;ş.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">16:00 Otellere d&ouml;n&uuml;ş.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">G&uuml;n&uuml;n ilk durağı, Ege&#39;ye giden nakliye yolunda Solimyalılar tarafından inşa edilen Termessos Antik Kenti olacaktır. Tamamen dağlık bir alana inşa edilmiş, duvarlar, Hadrianların zafer kemeri, sarnı&ccedil;lar, tiyatro, spor salonu, agora, Odeon ve Heroon gibi kalıntıların bir kısmını keşfetmek i&ccedil;in zaman harcayacağız. Uzak ve geniş alana dağılmış mezarlar arasında Alcates, Agatemeros &lsquo;un sıradışı yerleri ve Aslan bezeli lahitler g&ouml;r&uuml;lebilir.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Termessos, yaban ke&ccedil;isi ve geyiği yetiştirmek i&ccedil;in bir alan i&ccedil;eren ve Anadolu vaşağının son sığınağı olan G&uuml;ll&uuml;k Dağ Milli Parkı&#39;nda bulunmaktadır. Şanslıysak, burada yaşayan bir&ccedil;ok kelebeğe de rastlayabiliriz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Lezzetli bir &ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra Antalya&rsquo;da T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin bir şelalesi olan D&uuml;den Şelaleleri&#39;ni g&ouml;rmeye devam edeceğiz. D&uuml;den Nehri&#39;nin (G&uuml;ney Anadolu&rsquo;daki en b&uuml;y&uuml;k nehirlerden biri) oluşturduğu şelale, Antalya&#39;nın 12 km kuzey doğusunda, Aşağı D&uuml;den Şelaleleri&rsquo;nin berrak sularının doğrudan Akdeniz&#39;e kayalık u&ccedil;urumdan d&uuml;şmesiyle sona ermektedir.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Geziyle ge&ccedil;en b&uuml;y&uuml;k bir g&uuml;n&uuml;n ardından saat 17: 00&#39;de otelinize geri d&ouml;neceksiniz.</span></span></p>\n', '', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Otelden transfer hizmeti.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Konforlu klimalı minib&uuml;s ve profesyonel rehber eşliğinde seyahat edin.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Seyahat masrafı dahil edilmiştir.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&Ouml;ğle yemeği dahil, i&ccedil;ecekler dahil değildir.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Giriş &Uuml;cretleri dahildir.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Antalya merkez ofisi.</span></p>\n', '', '7 Saat', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">T&uuml;rk&ccedil;e konuşan rehber.</span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Turdan 24 saat &ouml;nce.</span></p>\n', '', 'Тур по водопаду Термессос и Дюден', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Маршрут и время тура указаны ниже:</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">09:00 Сбор и отправление в центральный офис Анталии Калейчи.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">09:50 Прибытие в древний город Термессос, Гюллюк, 40 км на северо-запад от Анталии.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">10:00 Через 30 минут мы отправимся на вершину древнего города Термессос. Спустя два часа после античной экскурсии по городу у нас будет 3 часа на Термессос.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">13:15 Возвращение в Анталию.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">14:00 Прибытие на водопад Дуден. Даётся один час на посещение Национального парка и перерыв на обед.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">15:30 Возвращение в Анталию.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">16:00 Возвращение в отели.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Первой остановкой дня станет древний город Термессос, построенный солимиалами по дороге к Эгейскому морю. Он полностью построен в гористой местности, мы проведём время, изучая некоторые из руин, такие как стены, триумфальные арки Адриана, водоёмы, театр, спортзал, агора, Одеон и Герун. Среди гробниц, разбросанных по отдалённой и обширной территории, можно увидеть алькатов, необычные места Агатемероса и саркофаги со львами.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Термессос расположен в Национальном парке горы Гюллюк, который является последним пристанищем анатолийской рыси и включает в себя территорию для выращивания диких коз и оленей. Если нам повезет, мы сможем встретить много бабочек, живущих в этой местности.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После вкусного обеда мы продолжим осматривать водопад Анталии в Турции, который называется Дюден. Этот водопад, образованный рекой Дюден (одна из крупнейших рек в южной Анатолии) и заканчивается в 12 км к северо-востоку от Анталии. Он демонстрирует свою красоту, с помощью своих чистых вод. Водопад Нижнего Дудена впадает со скалистого утеса прямо в Средиземное море.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После прекрасного дня и прогулок по достопримечательностям, вы вернетесь в свой отель в 17:00.</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Транспорт из отеля.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Путешествуйте комфортабельным микроавтобусом с кондиционером и профессиональным гидом</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Командировочные расходы / страховка включена.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Напитки не включены.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Входные билеты и обед включены.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Главный офис в Анталии.</span></span></p>\n', '', '7 часов', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Русско-язычный или англоязычный гид.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">За 24 часа до тура.</span></span></p>\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(38, 'Demre, Myra & Kekova Sunken City Tour', 'Demre-Myra--Kekova-Sunken-City-Tour', '51c92-kekova.jpg', '7cd93-myra-686x386.jpg', '2040', 26, '<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">07:00&nbsp;&nbsp; Meeting and move from Antalya Kalei&ccedil;i head office.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:\"><o:p></o:p></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">08:45&nbsp;&nbsp; Breakfast break with a unique view of Kumluca valley.</span></span></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">09:15&nbsp;&nbsp; Move to Demre.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:\"><o:p></o:p></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">10:30&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrival to the port of Demre Ucagiz is 150 km west of Antalya. The Boat tour takes one and a half hour. We will see the Simena Village, Castle and after followed to Kekova Island and Sunken City. In the direction of turning we take stop half an hour for swimming in Burc Bay. The boat trip ends again at Ucagiz and the bus moves to the center of Demre.</span></span></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">12:45&nbsp;&nbsp; Open buffet lunch at the restaurant in the center of Demre.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:\"><o:p></o:p></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">14:00&nbsp;&nbsp; Accompanied by our experienced guide we will visit St. Nicholas church in Demre and then move to Myra.</span></span></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">15:00&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrive in Myra and visit the Lycian Rock Tombs and Roman theater here. Then move to return to Antalya. </span></span></span></div>\n<div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);\">19:00&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrival to Antalya.</span></span></span></div>\n', '<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The road to Kekova harbor is very picturesque. On the left side you will see clean turquoise waters of the Mediterranean sea and on the right side you will pass small nice towns and the beautiful Taurus mountains. In Kekova you will join one hour boat trip to discover the ruins of the sunken city. The glass bottom boat sails slowly so you can clearly see the remains of many buildings under the sea, the stairs going under the water. The guide will explain you the history of this ancient Lycian city that you can imagine how it was looking before. On the mainland of Kekova island you will see the remaining walls and doors of the monumental foundations, one of them considered to be a Byzantine church. Lots of Lycian sarcophagus can be seen either on the mainland and in the sea. Don&#39;t miss the chance to swim in the clear turquoise waters during a swimming break.</span></span></div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">After an exciting cruise you will drive to the ancient city of Myra. It is very famous for the Lycian rock-cut tombs and its big amphitheater. You will have enough time to discover the every part of this ancient city and incredible Lycian necropolis. The last attractions to visit is the church of Saint Nicholas in Demre. Every year thousands of people from all around the world come here to see, touch and pray at the marble sarcophagus considered to be the original tomb of St. Nicholas. The church was restored some years ago and now serves as a museum. You will definitely enjoy its interior covered by relatively well preserved frescos.</span></span></div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Just near by the church there is a local restaurant where you will have an open buffet lunch. And then you will drive back to Antalya as the tour is finished. The approximate arrival time is 5 pm.</span></span></div>\n', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: var(--dark-blue); box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">Sports or walking shoes are preferred.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: var(--dark-blue); box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">Don&rsquo;t forget your swimwear and the sun cream.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Transfer service from the Hotel.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Travel with comfortable air conditioned minibus and the presence of a professional guide.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Travel incurence are included.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Kekova Boat tour is included and there is a half hour swimming stop.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Breakfast and Drinks are excluded.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Entrance Fees &amp; Lunch are inclusive.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Head office in Antalya.</span></span></p>\n', '', '12 Hours', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">English speaking tour guide.</span></p>\n', 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">24 Hours before the tour.</span></span></p>\n', 1, '', 'surekli', 0, '', 1, '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Demre, Myra &amp; Kekova Sunken City Tour&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">reakfast break with a unique view of Kumluca valley.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Move to Demre.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Arrival to the port of Demre Ucagiz is 150 km west of Antalya. The Boat tour takes one and a half hour. We will see the Simena Village, Castle and after followed to Kekova Island and Sunken City. In the direction of turning we take stop half an hour for swimming in Burc Bay. The boat trip ends again at Ucagiz and the bus moves to the center of Demre.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Open buffet lunch at the restaurant in the center of Demre.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Accompanied by our experienced guide we will visit St. Nicholas church in Demre and then move to Myra.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Arrive in Myra and visit the Lycian Rock Tombs and Roman theater here. Then move to return to Antalya.</span></p>\n', 1, 1, '13+', '6-12', '0-5', 0, 32, 'Demre, Myra & Kekova Sunken Şehri Turu', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">07:00 Antalya Kalei&ccedil;i merkez ofisinde toplanma ve hareket etme.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">08:45 Kumluca vadisinin eşsiz manzarası karşında kahvaltı molası.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">09:15 Demre&#39;ye gidiş.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">10:30 Antalya&#39;nın 150 km batısındaki Demre &Uuml;&ccedil;ağız Limanına varış.Tekne turu bir bu&ccedil;uk saat s&uuml;rer. Simena K&ouml;y&uuml;&#39;n&uuml;, Kalesi&#39;ni ve ardından Kekova Adası ve Batık Şehir&#39;i g&ouml;receğiz. D&ouml;n&uuml;ş y&ouml;n&uuml;nde Bur&ccedil; Koyu&#39;nda y&uuml;zmek i&ccedil;in yarım saat duracağız. Tekne turu &Uuml;&ccedil;ağız&#39;da tekrar sona eriyor ve otob&uuml;s Demre&#39;nin merkezine gidecek.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">12:45 Demre&#39;nin merkezindeki restoranda a&ccedil;ık b&uuml;fe &ouml;ğle yemeği.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">14:00 Tecr&uuml;beli rehberimiz eşliğinde Demre&#39;deki St. Nicholas kilisesini ziyaret edip Myra&#39;ya gideceiğiz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">15:00 Myra&#39;ya varınca burada Likya Kaya Mezarları ve Roma tiyatrosunu ziyaret edeceğiz. Ardından Antalya&#39;ya d&ouml;nmek i&ccedil;in harekete ge&ccedil;eceğiz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">19:00 Antalya&#39;ya varış.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Kekova limanına giden yol &ccedil;ok g&uuml;zeldir. Sol tarafta Akdeniz&#39;in turkuaz sularını g&ouml;receksiniz ve sağ tarafta k&uuml;&ccedil;&uuml;k g&uuml;zel kasabalardan ve g&uuml;zel Toros dağlarından ge&ccedil;eceksiniz. Kekova&#39;da batık şehir kalıntılarını keşfetmek i&ccedil;in bir saatlik tekne turuna katılacaksınız. Cam dibi teknesi yavaş&ccedil;a hareket eder b&ouml;ylece denizin altındaki bir&ccedil;ok yapının kalıntılarını, merdivenlerin suyun altına girdiğini net bir şekilde g&ouml;rebilirsiniz. Rehber, daha &ouml;nce nasıl g&ouml;r&uuml;nd&uuml;ğ&uuml;n&uuml; hayal edebileceğiniz bu antik Likya şehrinin tarihini anlatacaktır. Kekova Adası&rsquo;nın anakarasında biri Bizans kilisesi olarak kabul edilen anıtsal temellerin kalan duvarlarını ve kapılarını g&ouml;receksiniz. Anakarada ve denizde bir s&uuml;r&uuml; Likya lahitleri g&ouml;r&uuml;lebilir. Y&uuml;zme molası sırasında turkuaz sularda y&uuml;zme şansını ka&ccedil;ırmayın.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Heyecan verici bir yolculuktan sonra Myra antik kentine gideceksiniz. Likya kaya mezarları ve b&uuml;y&uuml;k amfitiyatrosu ile &uuml;nl&uuml;d&uuml;r. Bu antik kentin her yerini ve inanılmaz Likya nekropol&uuml;n&uuml; keşfetmek i&ccedil;in yeterli zamanınız olacaktır. Ziyaret edilecek son ilgi &ccedil;ekici yer Demre&#39;deki Saint Nicholas kilisesidir. Her yıl d&uuml;nyanın d&ouml;rt bir yanından binlerce insan, Aziz Nikolaos&#39;un orijinal mezarı olarak kabul edilen mermer lahitlere dokunmak ve dua etmek i&ccedil;in buraya geliyor. Kilise birka&ccedil; yıl &ouml;nce restore edildi ve şimdi m&uuml;ze olarak hizmet veriyor. Kesinlikle iyi korunmuş fresklerle kaplı i&ccedil; mekanının tadını &ccedil;ıkaracaksınız.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Kilisenin hemen yanında a&ccedil;ık b&uuml;fe &ouml;ğle yemeği yiyebileceğiniz yerel bir restoran bulunmaktadır. Ve tur bittikten sonra Antalya&#39;ya geri d&ouml;neceksiniz. Yaklaşık varış saati 17:00&rsquo;dir</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Spor ya da y&uuml;r&uuml;y&uuml;ş ayakkabısı tercih edilmelidir.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Mayonuzu ve g&uuml;neş kreminizi unutmayınız.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Konforlu klimalı minib&uuml;s ve profesyonel rehber ile seyahat edin.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Seyahat masrafı dahildir.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Kekova Tekne turu dahildir ve y&uuml;zme molası yarım saat s&uuml;rmektedir.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Kahvaltı ve i&ccedil;ecekler dahil değildir.</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Giriş &Uuml;cretleri ve &Ouml;ğle Yemeği dahildir.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Antalya merkez ofisi.</span></p>\n', '', '12 Saat', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">T&uuml;rk&ccedil;e konuşan rehber.</span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Turdan 24 saat &ouml;nce.</span></p>\n', '', 'Городская экскурсия по Демре, Майра и затонувший город Кекова', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">07:00 Встреча и прибытие в центральный офис Анталии Калейчи.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">08:45 Перерыв на завтрак с неповторимым видом на долину Кумлука.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">09:15 Отправление в Демре.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">10:30 Прибытие в порт Демре Учагыз. Он находится в 150 км к западу от Анталии. Мы посетим деревню Симена, замок, а затем остров Кекова и затонувший город. Мы остановимся на полчаса, чтобы поплыть по направлению к заливу Бурч. Экскурсия на лодке снова заканчивается в Учагыз, и автобус отправится в центр Демре.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">12:45 Фуршет в ресторане в центре Демре.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">14:00 С помощью нашего опытного гида мы посетим церковь Св.Николая в Демре и отправимся в Мира.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">15:00 Когда мы приедем в Мира, мы посетим ликийские скальные гробницы и римский театр. После этого мы вернёмся в Анталию.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">19:00 Прибытие в Анталию.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Дорога в порт Кекова очень красивая. С левой стороны вы увидите бирюзовые воды Средиземного моря и пройдете через маленькие красивые городки и прекрасные горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус) справа. В Кекова вы посетите часовую экскурсию на лодке, осматривая и изучая руины затонувшего города. Лодка со стеклянным дном движется медленно, так что вы сможете чётко увидеть остатки многих зданий под морем, лестница идет под водой. Гид расскажет вам историю этого древнего ликийского города, где вы можете представить, как он выглядел раньше. На материке острова Кекова вы увидите оставшиеся стены и ворота монументальных фундаментов, одна из которых считается византийской церковью. Много ликийских саркофагов можно увидеть на материке и на море. Не упустите шанс поплавать в бирюзовых водах во время перерыва для плаванья.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После увлекательного путешествия вы отправитесь в древний город Мира. Он славится ликийскими скальными гробницами и большим амфитеатром. У вас будет достаточно времени, чтобы осмотреть этот древний город и его невероятный ликийский некрополь. Последняя достопримечательность, которую стоит посетить, - это церковь Святого Николая в Демре. Каждый год тысячи людей со всего мира приезжают сюда, чтобы потрогать и помолиться мраморному саркофагу, который считается подлинной гробницей святителя Николая. Церковь была восстановлена несколько лет назад и сейчас служит музеем. Вам наверняка понравятся интерьер с фресками, который был несколько лет назад отреставрирован.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Рядом с церковью есть местный ресторан, где вы можете насладиться обедом &quot;шведский стол&quot;. И как только тур закончится, вы вернетесь в Анталию. Приблизительное время прибытия 17:00</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Обуйте предпочтительно спортивную или прогулочную обувь.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Не забудьте взять купальник и солнцезащитный крем.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Путешествуйте в комфортабельном микроавтобусе с кондиционером и профессиональным гидом.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Дорога включена.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Экскурсия на лодке в Кекова включена, и плавательный перерыв занимают полчаса.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Завтрак и напитки не включены.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Входные билеты и обед включены.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Главный офис в Анталии.</span></span></p>\n', '', '12 часов', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Русско-язычный или англоязычный гид.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">За 24 часа до тура.</span></span></p>\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '');
