(86, 'Nemrut Tours From Cappadocia 3 Days', 'Nemrut-Tours-From-Cappadocia-3-Days', '00ba6-nemrut.jpg', 'a88da-nemrut-4.jpg', '8120', 39, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Cappadocia is one of the most surreal, stunning and visited parts of Turkey. The landscapes and cave cities are unique, and worth the particularly long effort it can take to travel to the region. But where do you go after you&rsquo;ve explored the underground cities and floated above the valleys in a hot air balloon?</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">A not so visited, but equally magnificent and unique place to see is Mount Nemrut- or&nbsp;<em><a href=\"http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/448\" target=\"_blank\">Nemrut Dagi</a></em>. This UNESCO World Heritage Site is the lasting memorial to an egotistical king of old. A man who had statues of himself and his family built on top of the tallest mountain in his Kingdom and surrounded by Gods. The views from the top are glorious, and the giant heads of the now decapitated statues are a curious sight.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">The only problem is that Mount Nemrut is nowhere near anything at all. The closest attraction is Cappadocia. If you make it that far into the interior of Turkey, it&rsquo;s well worth the trip to Mount Nemrut as well.</span></span></p>\n<h4>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">DAY 1: Cappadocia - Kahramanmaras - Kahta</span></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Meet the guide and driver in the hotel at 08:00am, and depart from G&ouml;reme. After passing Kayseri, we visit the&nbsp;<strong>Seljuk Karatayhan Caravanserai</strong>&nbsp;on the famous Silk Road. We then drive for lunch through the Taurus Mountains, affording us the opportunity to observe the countryside and everyday life of rural&nbsp;<strong>Turkey.</strong>&nbsp;After lunch we drive to Kahramanmaras for a different experience-tasting best ice-cream in Turkey. We then drive to Kahta and check-in our hotel. Overnight in Kahta.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">DAY 2: Adıyaman - Mt.Nemrut - Harran - Sanlıurfa</span></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">We depart from hotel very early in the morning up to the&nbsp;<strong>Mount Nemrut.</strong>&nbsp;At the end of the road, we get off the van and walk twenty-five minutes until the summit. Here we watch the memorable sun rise between the colossal size statues and heads of the kings and Gods. We then visit Arsemia which was once the capital of the Commagene&nbsp;Kingdom before continues to the ancient Septimus Severus Bridge over the Cendere stream, and the Karakus tumulus where members of the royal family were buried. We keep driving to Sanliurfa and Harran. We visit the&nbsp;<strong>Ataturk Dam</strong>&nbsp;which is the biggest dam in the Middle East, en route. We check-in the hotel in Sanliurfa and have lunch there.&nbsp;<strong>Gobeklitepe</strong>&nbsp;which is a hilltop sanctuary erected on the highest point of an elongated mountain ridge some 15 km northeast of the town of Sanlıurfa. This sanctuary is proved by the archaeologists that it is the oldest sanctuary in the world which is about 11,500 years old. After lunch we visit Abraham&#39;s Cave and the Pools of Holy Carp surrounding it. We than walk around oriental covered bazaar and G&uuml;mr&uuml;khan. We drive to&nbsp;<strong>Harran</strong>&nbsp;a village of Mud-Brick &quot;beehive&quot; houses mentioned in the book of genesis where Abraham spent the last years of his life. Dinner and overnight in Sanliurfa.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">DAY 3: Sanlıurfa - Cappadocia</span></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">After breakfast we depart from&nbsp;<strong>Sanliurfa</strong>&nbsp;to Birecik which is famous for its bald-ibis (Kelaynak) birds. These birds are living only in Birecik in the world and there is a very limited population of them. We visit the breeding farm of Bald Ibis birds. After our lunch, we drive up to the Taurus Mountains. We have a short tea break and drive back to&nbsp;<strong>G&ouml;reme.</strong></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 43, 73);\">INCLUDED</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Hotel pick up &amp; drop off by air-conditioned non-smoking tour coaches</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Entrance fees</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Professional licensed tour guide</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Service charges &amp; local taxes</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Hotels</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p font-size:=\"\" helvetica=\"\" segoe=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0.25rem 0px; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; color: rgb(26, 43, 73);\">\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">​<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">EXCLUDED</span></span></span></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Dinner, beverage</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Personal expenses</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Tips &amp; gratitues</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Pick up from hotel or airport in cappadocia.</span></span></p>\n', '', '3 Days', 0, '1', '', 0, 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">English speaking tour guide.</span></span></p>\n', 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">7&nbsp; Days before the tours.</span></span></p>\n', 1, '', 'surekli', 0, '1', 1, '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Cappadocia is one of the most surreal, stunning and visited parts of Turkey. The landscapes and cave cities are unique, and worth the particularly long effort it can take to travel to the region. But where do you go after you&rsquo;ve explored the underground cities and floated above the valleys in a hot air balloon?</span></p>\n', 0, 1, '', '', '0-5', 1, 54, 'Kapadokya\'dan 3 Günlük Nemrut Turu', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Kapadokya, T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin en ger&ccedil;ek&uuml;st&uuml;, etkileyici ve ziyaret edilen b&ouml;lgelerinden biridir. Manzaralar ve mağara şehirleri benzersizdir ve b&ouml;lgeye seyahat etmek i&ccedil;in harcayabileceğiniz &ouml;zel &ccedil;abalara değer. Peki yeraltı şehirlerini keşfettikten ve sıcak hava balonunda vadilerin &uuml;zerinde u&ccedil;tuktan sonra nereye gidiyorsunuz?</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Nemrut Dağı ,&ccedil;ok ziyaret edilmemiş fakat aynı zamanda g&ouml;rkemli ve eşsiz bir yerdir.&nbsp; Bu dağda UNESCO D&uuml;nya Mirası Listesinde yer alan eski bencil bir kralın kalıcı anıtı vardır. Kralın ve ailesinin tanrılarla &ccedil;evrili heykelleri Krallığı&#39;ndaki en y&uuml;ksek dağın tepesine inşa ettirilmiş. Tepeden manzaralar şahane ve kesik başlı heykellerin de dev kafaları merak uyandıran bir manzara sunuyor.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Tek sorun Nemrut Dağı&rsquo;nın hi&ccedil;bir yere yakın olmamasıdır. En yakın nokta Kapadokya&#39;dır. T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin o kadar i&ccedil;indeyseniz, Nemrut Dağı&rsquo;na da yolculuk yapmaya değer.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">1. G&Uuml;N: Kapadokya - Kahramanmaraş - Kahta</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Otelde rehber ve şof&ouml;rle sabah 08: 00&#39;de buluşup G&ouml;reme&#39;den hareket edeceğiz. Kayseri&#39;yi ge&ccedil;tikten sonra &uuml;nl&uuml; İpek Yolu &uuml;zerindeki Sel&ccedil;uklu Karatayhan Kervansarayı&#39;nı ziyaret edeceğiz. Daha sonra Toros Dağları&#39;nda &ouml;ğle yemeğine &ccedil;ıkıp, kırsal b&ouml;lgeyi ve kırsal T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin g&uuml;nl&uuml;k hayatını g&ouml;zlemleme fırsatı bulacağız. &Ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra, farklı bir tadım deneyimi ile T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin en iyi dondurması i&ccedil;in Kahramanmaraş&#39;a gideceğiz. Daha sonra Kahta&#39;ya gidip otelimize giriş yaptıracağız. Geceyi Kahta&#39;da ge&ccedil;ireceğiz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">2. G&Uuml;N: Adıyaman - Bayram - Harran - Şanlıurfa</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Sabah erkenden otelden ayrılıp, Nemrut Dağı&#39;na kadar ilerleyeceğiz. Yolun sonunda, minib&uuml;sten inip ve zirveye kadar yirmi beş dakika y&uuml;r&uuml;yeceğiz. Burada devasa boyut heykelleri ile kralların ve tanrıların başları arasındaki unutulmaz g&uuml;neşin doğuşunu izleyeceğiz. Daha sonra, bir zamanlar Kommagene Krallığı&#39;nın başkenti olan Arsemia&#39;yı, Cendere Deresi &uuml;zerindeki Antik Septimus Severus K&ouml;pr&uuml;s&uuml;&#39;n&uuml; ve kraliyet ailesinin &uuml;yelerinin g&ouml;m&uuml;l&uuml; olduğu Karakus T&uuml;m&uuml;l&uuml;s&uuml;&#39;n&uuml; ziyaret edeceğiz. Şanlıurfa ve Harran&#39;a doğru yol alacağız. Orta Doğu&#39;daki en b&uuml;y&uuml;k baraj olan Atat&uuml;rk Barajı&#39;nı ziyaret edeceğiz. Şanlıurfa&#39;daki otelde giriş yapıp &ouml;ğle yemeği yiyeceğiz. Tepedeki bir sığınak olan G&ouml;beklitepe, Şanlıurfa il&ccedil;esinin yaklaşık 15 km kuzeydoğusunda, uzun bir dağ sırtının en y&uuml;ksek noktasına inşa edilmiştir. Bu kutsal alan arkeologlar tarafından d&uuml;nyanın yaklaşık 11.500 yıllık en eski sığınak olduğunu kanıtlamıştır. &Ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra, İbrahim&#39;in Mağarasını ve etrafındaki Kutsal Sazan Havuzları&#39;nı ziyaret edeceğiz. Sonra Oryantal &ccedil;arşı ve G&uuml;mr&uuml;khan &ccedil;evresinde dolaşacağız. Harran&#39;a, İbrahim&#39;in hayatının son yıllarını harcadığı soy kitabında adı ge&ccedil;en &Ccedil;amur-Tuğla &quot;arı kovanı&quot; evlerinden oluşan bir k&ouml;ye gideceğiz. Son olarak Şanlıurfa&#39;da akşam yemeğini yiyip geceyi burda &ccedil;ireceğiz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">3. G&Uuml;N: Şanlıurfa - Kapadokya</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Kahvaltıdan sonra Şanlıurfa&#39;dan, kelaynak kuşları ile &uuml;nl&uuml; Birecik&#39;e hareket edeceğiz. Bu kuşlar d&uuml;nyada sadece Birecik&#39;te yaşıyor ve &ccedil;ok sınırlı bir n&uuml;fusu var. Kelaynak kuşlarının &uuml;reme &ccedil;iftliğini ziyaret edeceğiz. &Ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra Toros Dağları&#39;na &ccedil;ıkacağız. Sonra kısa bir &ccedil;ay molamız olacak ve G&ouml;reme&#39;ye geri d&ouml;neceğiz.</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<u><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Bu tura ne dahildir?&nbsp;</span></span></strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Profesyonel rehber</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">t&uuml;m giriş &uuml;cretleri</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">t&uuml;m ulaşımlar</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<u><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Bu tura dahil olmayanlar</span></span></strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Akşam yemeği ve i&ccedil;ecekler</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">kişisel masraflar</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">bahşişler</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Otelden servis.</span></p>\n', '', '3 Günlük', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">T&uuml;rk&ccedil;e konuşan rehber.</span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Turdan 7 g&uuml;n &ouml;nce.</span></p>\n', '', '3-дневный тур из Каппадокии в Немрут', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Каппадокия - это необыкновенное место и одно из самых впечатляющих и наиболее посещаемых в Турции. Пейзажи и пещерные города уникальны и их стоит посетить. Итак, куда вы отправляетесь после открытия подземных городов и полетов над долинами на воздушном шаре?</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Гора Немрут - это малопосещаемое, но в то же время это великолепное и уникальное место. Эта гора имеет вечный памятник старому эгоистичному королю, который включен в список всемирного наследия ЮНЕСКО. Статуи короля и его семьи были построены на вершине самой высокой горы в королевстве. На вершине распростились великолепные пейзажи скульптур гигантских обрезанных голов.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Единственная проблема в том, что гора Немрут находится далеко. Ближайшее к ней место - это Каппадокия. Если вы находитесь в Турции, то вам обязательно стоит посетить гору Немрут.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">ДЕНЬ 1: Каппадокия - Кахраманмараш &ndash; Кахта</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Мы встретимся с гидом и водителем в 08:00 в отеле и выедем из Гёреме. Проедем через Кайсери, посетим караван-сарай Сельджук Каратайхан на знаменитом Шелковом пути. Затем перейдем на обед в горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус), а также вам предоставится возможность понаблюдать за повседневной сельской жизнью Турции. После обеда отправимся в Кахраманмараш для того, чтобы попробовать самое лучшее в Турции мороженое. Затем мы поедем в Кахту и зарегистрируемся в нашем отеле. Мы проведем ночь в Кахте.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">ДЕНЬ 2: Адыяман - Байрам - Харран &ndash; Шанлыурфа</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Рано утром мы покинем отель и продолжим путь к горе Немрут. В конце нашего пути мы выйдем из автобуса и пройдем двадцать пять минут до пика горы. Здесь мы встретим восход солнца между статуями огромных размеров, головами королей и богов. Позже посетим Арсемию, столицу Королевства Коммаген, древний мост Септимус Северус на ручье Сендере и Каракус Тумулус, где похоронены члены королевской семьи. Мы отправимся в Шанлыурфу и Харран. Посетим плотину Ататюрка, самую большую плотину на Ближнем Востоке. Затем пообедаем в отеле в Шанлыурфе. Гёбеклитепе - это место на холме, было построено в самой высокой точке длинного горного хребта, примерно в 15 км к северо-востоку от города Шанлыурфа. Археологи доказали, что это священное место было самым старым местом в мире и ему примерно 11 500 лет. После обеда мы посетим пещеру Авраама и бассейны Святого Карпа около него. Затем мы прогуляемся по центру восточного рынка и Гюмрюкхан. После этого мы пойдем в Харран, деревню, состоящую из домов-улей из грязевого кирпича, упомянутых в последней книге жизни Авраама. Наконец, мы поужинаем в Шанлыурфе и проведем здесь ночь.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">ДЕНЬ 3: Шанлыурфа &ndash; Каппадокия</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После завтрака мы переедем из Шанлыурфы в Биреджик, известный своими лысыми птицами. Эти птицы живут только в Биреджике и в мире их количество ограниченно. Мы собираемся посетить ферму где размножаются лесные ибисы. После обеда мы поедем в горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус). Затем у нас будет небольшой перерыв на чай и мы вернемся в Гёреме.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После обеда отправится в горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус). Затем у нас будет небольшой перерыв на чай и мы вернемся в Гёреме.</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong><u>Что входит в этот тур?</u></strong></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Профессиональный гид</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Все входные билеты</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Весь транспорт</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong><u>Что не входит в этот тур</u></strong></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Ужин и напитки</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Личные расходы</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Чаевые</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Сервис из отеля</span></span></p>\n', '', '3 дня', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Русско-язычный или англоязычный гид.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">За 7 дней до тура.</span></span></p>\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(92, 'Nemrut Tour From Cappadocia 3 Days', 'Nemrut-Tour-From-Cappadocia-3-Days', '00ba6-nemrut.jpg', 'a88da-nemrut-4.jpg', '1310', 23, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Cappadocia is one of the most surreal, stunning and visited parts of Turkey. The landscapes and cave cities are unique, and worth the particularly long effort it can take to travel to the region. But where do you go after you&rsquo;ve explored the underground cities and floated above the valleys in a hot air balloon?</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">A not so visited, but equally magnificent and unique place to see is Mount Nemrut- or&nbsp;<em><a href=\"http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/448\" target=\"_blank\">Nemrut Dagi</a></em>. This UNESCO World Heritage Site is the lasting memorial to an egotistical king of old. A man who had statues of himself and his family built on top of the tallest mountain in his Kingdom and surrounded by Gods. The views from the top are glorious, and the giant heads of the now decapitated statues are a curious sight.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">The only problem is that Mount Nemrut is nowhere near anything at all. The closest attraction is Cappadocia. If you make it that far into the interior of Turkey, it&rsquo;s well worth the trip to Mount Nemrut as well.</span></span></p>\n<h4>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">DAY 1: Cappadocia - Kahramanmaras - Kahta</span></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Meet the guide and driver in the hotel at 08:00am, and depart from G&ouml;reme. After passing Kayseri, we visit the&nbsp;<strong>Seljuk Karatayhan Caravanserai</strong>&nbsp;on the famous Silk Road. We then drive for lunch through the Taurus Mountains, affording us the opportunity to observe the countryside and everyday life of rural&nbsp;<strong>Turkey.</strong>&nbsp;After lunch we drive to Kahramanmaras for a different experience-tasting best ice-cream in Turkey. We then drive to Kahta and check-in our hotel. Overnight in Kahta.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">DAY 2: Adıyaman - Mt.Nemrut - Harran - Sanlıurfa</span></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">We depart from hotel very early in the morning up to the&nbsp;<strong>Mount Nemrut.</strong>&nbsp;At the end of the road, we get off the van and walk twenty-five minutes until the summit. Here we watch the memorable sun rise between the colossal size statues and heads of the kings and Gods. We then visit Arsemia which was once the capital of the Commagene&nbsp;Kingdom before continues to the ancient Septimus Severus Bridge over the Cendere stream, and the Karakus tumulus where members of the royal family were buried. We keep driving to Sanliurfa and Harran. We visit the&nbsp;<strong>Ataturk Dam</strong>&nbsp;which is the biggest dam in the Middle East, en route. We check-in the hotel in Sanliurfa and have lunch there.&nbsp;<strong>Gobeklitepe</strong>&nbsp;which is a hilltop sanctuary erected on the highest point of an elongated mountain ridge some 15 km northeast of the town of Sanlıurfa. This sanctuary is proved by the archaeologists that it is the oldest sanctuary in the world which is about 11,500 years old. After lunch we visit Abraham&#39;s Cave and the Pools of Holy Carp surrounding it. We than walk around oriental covered bazaar and G&uuml;mr&uuml;khan. We drive to&nbsp;<strong>Harran</strong>&nbsp;a village of Mud-Brick &quot;beehive&quot; houses mentioned in the book of genesis where Abraham spent the last years of his life. Dinner and overnight in Sanliurfa.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">DAY 3: Sanlıurfa - Cappadocia</span></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">After breakfast we depart from&nbsp;<strong>Sanliurfa</strong>&nbsp;to Birecik which is famous for its bald-ibis (Kelaynak) birds. These birds are living only in Birecik in the world and there is a very limited population of them. We visit the breeding farm of Bald Ibis birds. After our lunch, we drive up to the Taurus Mountains. We have a short tea break and drive back to&nbsp;<strong>G&ouml;reme.</strong></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 43, 73);\">INCLUDED</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Hotel pick up &amp; drop off by air-conditioned non-smoking tour coaches</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Entrance fees</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Professional licensed tour guide</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Service charges &amp; local taxes</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Hotels</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p font-size:=\"\" helvetica=\"\" segoe=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0.25rem 0px; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; color: rgb(26, 43, 73); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \">\n	<span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">​<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">EXCLUDED</span></span></span></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Dinner, beverage</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Personal expenses</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Tips &amp; gratitues</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Pick up from hotel or airport in cappadocia.</span></span></p>\n', '', '3 Days', 0, '1', '', 0, 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">English speaking tour guide.</span></span></p>\n', 0, '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">7&nbsp; Days before the tours.</span></span></p>\n', 1, '', 'surekli', 0, '1', 0, '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Equally magnificent and unique place to see is Mount Nemrut- or Nemrut Dagi. 3 days history tour.</span></span></p>\n', 1, 1, '', '', '0-5', 1, 55, 'Kapadokya\'dan 3 Günlük Nemrut Turu', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Kapadokya, T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin en ger&ccedil;ek&uuml;st&uuml;, etkileyici ve ziyaret edilen b&ouml;lgelerinden biridir. Manzaralar ve mağara şehirleri benzersizdir ve b&ouml;lgeye seyahat etmek i&ccedil;in harcayabileceğiniz &ouml;zel &ccedil;abalara değer. Peki yeraltı şehirlerini keşfettikten ve sıcak hava balonunda vadilerin &uuml;zerinde u&ccedil;tuktan sonra nereye gidiyorsunuz?</span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Nemrut Dağı ,&ccedil;ok ziyaret edilmemiş fakat aynı zamanda g&ouml;rkemli ve eşsiz bir yerdir.&nbsp; Bu dağda UNESCO D&uuml;nya Mirası Listesinde yer alan eski bencil bir kralın kalıcı anıtı vardır. Kralın ve ailesinin tanrılarla &ccedil;evrili heykelleri Krallığı&#39;ndaki en y&uuml;ksek dağın tepesine inşa ettirilmiş. Tepeden manzaralar şahane ve kesik başlı heykellerin de dev kafaları merak uyandıran bir manzara sunuyor.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Tek sorun Nemrut Dağı&rsquo;nın hi&ccedil;bir yere yakın olmamasıdır. En yakın nokta Kapadokya&#39;dır. T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin o kadar i&ccedil;indeyseniz, Nemrut Dağı&rsquo;na da yolculuk yapmaya değer.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">1. G&Uuml;N: Kapadokya - Kahramanmaraş - Kahta</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Otelde rehber ve şof&ouml;rle sabah 08: 00&#39;de buluşup G&ouml;reme&#39;den hareket edeceğiz. Kayseri&#39;yi ge&ccedil;tikten sonra &uuml;nl&uuml; İpek Yolu &uuml;zerindeki Sel&ccedil;uklu Karatayhan Kervansarayı&#39;nı ziyaret edeceğiz. Daha sonra Toros Dağları&#39;nda &ouml;ğle yemeğine &ccedil;ıkıp, kırsal b&ouml;lgeyi ve kırsal T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin g&uuml;nl&uuml;k hayatını g&ouml;zlemleme fırsatı bulacağız. &Ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra, farklı bir tadım deneyimi ile T&uuml;rkiye&#39;nin en iyi dondurması i&ccedil;in Kahramanmaraş&#39;a gideceğiz. Daha sonra Kahta&#39;ya gidip otelimize giriş yaptıracağız. Geceyi Kahta&#39;da ge&ccedil;ireceğiz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">2. G&Uuml;N: Adıyaman - Bayram - Harran - Şanlıurfa</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Sabah erkenden otelden ayrılıp, Nemrut Dağı&#39;na kadar ilerleyeceğiz. Yolun sonunda, minib&uuml;sten inip ve zirveye kadar yirmi beş dakika y&uuml;r&uuml;yeceğiz. Burada devasa boyut heykelleri ile kralların ve tanrıların başları arasındaki unutulmaz g&uuml;neşin doğuşunu izleyeceğiz. Daha sonra, bir zamanlar Kommagene Krallığı&#39;nın başkenti olan Arsemia&#39;yı, Cendere Deresi &uuml;zerindeki Antik Septimus Severus K&ouml;pr&uuml;s&uuml;&#39;n&uuml; ve kraliyet ailesinin &uuml;yelerinin g&ouml;m&uuml;l&uuml; olduğu Karakus T&uuml;m&uuml;l&uuml;s&uuml;&#39;n&uuml; ziyaret edeceğiz. Şanlıurfa ve Harran&#39;a doğru yol alacağız. Orta Doğu&#39;daki en b&uuml;y&uuml;k baraj olan Atat&uuml;rk Barajı&#39;nı ziyaret edeceğiz. Şanlıurfa&#39;daki otelde giriş yapıp &ouml;ğle yemeği yiyeceğiz. Tepedeki bir sığınak olan G&ouml;beklitepe, Şanlıurfa il&ccedil;esinin yaklaşık 15 km kuzeydoğusunda, uzun bir dağ sırtının en y&uuml;ksek noktasına inşa edilmiştir. Bu kutsal alan arkeologlar tarafından d&uuml;nyanın yaklaşık 11.500 yıllık en eski sığınak olduğunu kanıtlamıştır. &Ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra, İbrahim&#39;in Mağarasını ve etrafındaki Kutsal Sazan Havuzları&#39;nı ziyaret edeceğiz. Sonra Oryantal &ccedil;arşı ve G&uuml;mr&uuml;khan &ccedil;evresinde dolaşacağız. Harran&#39;a, İbrahim&#39;in hayatının son yıllarını harcadığı soy kitabında adı ge&ccedil;en &Ccedil;amur-Tuğla &quot;arı kovanı&quot; evlerinden oluşan bir k&ouml;ye gideceğiz. Son olarak Şanlıurfa&#39;da akşam yemeğini yiyip geceyi burda &ccedil;ireceğiz.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">3. G&Uuml;N: Şanlıurfa - Kapadokya</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Kahvaltıdan sonra Şanlıurfa&#39;dan, kelaynak kuşları ile &uuml;nl&uuml; Birecik&#39;e hareket edeceğiz. Bu kuşlar d&uuml;nyada sadece Birecik&#39;te yaşıyor ve &ccedil;ok sınırlı bir n&uuml;fusu var. Kelaynak kuşlarının &uuml;reme &ccedil;iftliğini ziyaret edeceğiz. &Ouml;ğle yemeğinden sonra Toros Dağları&#39;na &ccedil;ıkacağız. Sonra kısa bir &ccedil;ay molamız olacak ve G&ouml;reme&#39;ye geri d&ouml;neceğiz.</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<u><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Bu tura ne dahildir?&nbsp;</span></span></strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Profesyonel rehber</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">t&uuml;m giriş &uuml;cretleri</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">t&uuml;m ulaşımlar</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	<u><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Bu tura dahil olmayanlar</span></span></strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Akşam yemeği ve i&ccedil;ecekler</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">kişisel masraflar</span></span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">bahşişler</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Otelden servis.</span></p>\n', '', '3 Günlük', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">T&uuml;rk&ccedil;e konuşan rehber.</span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Turdan 7 g&uuml;n &ouml;nce.</span></p>\n', '', '3-дневный тур из Каппадокии в Немрут', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Каппадокия - это необыкновенное место и одно из самых впечатляющих и наиболее посещаемых в Турции. Пейзажи и пещерные города уникальны и их стоит посетить. Итак, куда вы отправляетесь после открытия подземных городов и полётов над долинами на воздушном шаре?</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong>Гора Немрут</strong> - это малопосещаемое, но в то же время это великолепное и уникальное место. Эта гора имеет вечный памятник старому эгоистичному королю, который включен в список всемирного наследия ЮНЕСКО. Статуи короля и его семьи были построены на вершине самой высокой горы в королевстве. На вершине распростёрлись великолепные пейзажи скульптур гигантских обрезанных голов.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Единственная проблема в том, что гора Немрут находится далеко. Ближайшее к ней место - это Каппадокия. Если вы находитесь в Турции, то вам обязательно стоит посетить гору Немрут.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">ДЕНЬ 1: Каппадокия - Кахраманмараш - Кахта</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Мы встретимся с гидом и водителем в 08:00 в отеле и выедем из Гёреме. Проедем через Кайсери, посетим караван-сарай Сельджук Каратайхан на знаменитом Шелковом пути. Затем перейдем на обед в горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус), а также вам предоставится возможность понаблюдать за&nbsp; повседневной сельской жизнью Турции. После обеда отправимся в Кахраманмараш для того, чтобы попробовать самое лучшее в Турции мороженое. Затем мы поедем в Кахту и зарегистрируемся в нашем отеле. Мы проведём ночь в Кахте.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong>ДЕНЬ 2</strong>: Адыяман - Байрам - Харран - Шанлыурфа</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Рано утром мы покинем отель и продолжим путь к горе Немрут. В конце нашего пути мы выйдем из автобуса и пройдем двадцать пять минут до пика горы. Здесь мы встретим восход солнца между статуями огромных размеров, головами королей и богов. Позже посетим Арсемию, столицу Королевства Коммаген, древний мост Септимус Северус на ручье Сендере и Каракус Тумулус, где похоронены члены королевской семьи. Мы отправимся в Шанлыурфу и Харран. Посетим плотину Ататюрка, самую большую плотину на Ближнем Востоке. Затем пообедаем в отеле в Шанлыурфе. Гёбеклитепе - это место на холме, было построено в самой высокой точке длинного горного хребта, примерно в 15 км к северо-востоку от города Шанлыурфа. Археологи доказали, что это священное место было самым старым местом в мире и ему примерно 11 500 лет. После обеда мы посетим пещеру Авраама и бассейны Святого Карпа около него. Затем мы прогуляемся по центру восточного рынка и Гюмрюкхан. После этого мы пойдем в Харран, деревню, состоящую из домов-улей из грязевого кирпича, упомянутых в последней книге жизни Авраама. Наконец, мы поужинаем в Шанлыурфе и проведем здесь ночь.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong>ДЕНЬ 3</strong>: Шанлыурфа - Каппадокия</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После завтрака мы переедем из Шанлыурфы в Биреджик, известный своими лысыми птицами. Эти птицы живут только в Биреджике и в мире их количество ограниченно. Мы собираемся посетить ферму где размножаются лесные ибисы. После обеда мы поедем в горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус). Затем у нас будет небольшой перерыв на чай и мы вернемся в Гёреме.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">После обеда отправимся в горы Тавр (Торос или Таурус). Затем у нас будет небольшой перерыв на чай и мы вернемся в Гёреме.</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong><u>Что входит в этот тур?</u></strong></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Профессиональный гид</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Все входные билеты</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Весь транспорт</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\"><strong><u>Что не входит в этот тур</u></strong></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Ужин и напитки</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Личные расходы</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">&bull; Чаевые</span></span></p>\n', '', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif;\">Сервис из отеля.&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">3 дня</span></p>\n', '3 дня', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">Русско-язычный или англоязычный гид.</span></span></p>\n', '<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif;\">За 7 дней до тура.</span></span></p>\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '');
